< text>
On September 15, 2014 my Father brought in his 2007 Volvo to get a simple oil change. He brings his car to get an oil change every 5,000 miles as recommended. When he brought the car in, it was documented that there was nothing wrong with the car. As he drove him he heard strange sounds from the engine. Upon returning home he found oil all over underneath the car. When he tried to start the engine again it made a loud screeching sound that was deafening to the ears. The car wouldn't move, it was inoperable, and the engine was blown. He called Jiffy Lube to tell them what happened and they told him that he needed to bring it to a mechanic, and that they didn't do anything wrong to the car. With further persuasion they sent out a representative to look at the car while it was still at their house. By the time their representative arrived it was already loaded onto a tow truck, and ready to be towed into the Volvo dealership for further inspection. Jiffy Lube's representative went underneath the car without the permission of my Father, tools in hand, and tinkered with something under the car. Of course we are fearful that he was covering up something they had done wrong. The car went to the dealership, the Volvo mechanic's review of the car was that someone (Jiffy Lube), must have emptied the car of oil, and then ran the engine because there were shards of metal laced into the oil. Not only that but the oil in the car seemed to be dirty as well. The engine was shot, and it was in correlation due to something that had been done at Jiffy Lube. We reached out to Angel Torres, District Manager and reported what happened, he came out and looked at the car at the dealership and heard their review of what they thought had happened. He spoke to the employees that worked on the car and they confirmed that nothing was wrong with the car when it came in. He says that his employee that worked on the car denys anything going wrong while he worked on the car. Angel asked my Parents for proof that they had been maintaining the car properly (of course looking for a reason why this wasn't their fault). We found all of our records and have taken impeccable care of the car, and it was perfectly fine when my Father brought it in. Angel told us today that his employee says he did nothing wrong, and there's no proof that they caused the engine to die, and that he can't do anything for us. To help you imagine how we feel, consider what it would be like to go get your hair cut and colored, you leave the salon, and later at home you find that your hair is falling out in large clumps. You call the salon to report the problem, and they tell you that it isn't because of something they did. Now you understand. We are going to pursue legal action against Jiffy Lube. We do not recommend you go to this Jiffy Lube or any other for that matter. My Mom is disabled and very sick, she can't be left home without a car in case of emergency. My Father needs to go to work and so he has to take the one car they have now. My family has been put in a horrible situation because of their mistakes, and they have been left without any help.</text>

< text>
As a graduate of this program I can confidently say that this treatment center is not for everyone. If you are not ready to work hard, do a ton of clinical work, and be evaluated and assessed from top to bottom, this will not be a place that you enjoy. If you‚Äôre looking for a spa to go relax at, please move on and look elsewhere. Sure you get massages and surf lessons; yes, you get to play with wolves and horses and all of the yoga, acupuncture and beautiful sunsets you can stand...but at the end of the day these people mean business. This is a hard program that demands devotion, commitment, and surrender. The majority of people that were there, and very serious about changing their lives and improving themselves did fantastic and loved it! The other 10%, the ones that wanted all the benefits but weren‚Äôt willing to do the work to get them, they only lasted about a week. Like I said, it‚Äôs definitely not for everyone.<//text>

Had a manic episode that lasted months. Ruined my marriage, ruined my relationship with my gf in Monterey and strained my relationship w/my family, ruined my relationship with my daughter. Strained & ruined many relationships with friends...too many to mention. Lost my job at DOLE! I can only humbly ask for their forgiveness one day.

Overa 6 month manic episode, I had Multiple arrests, alcohol, drugs & women. Smuggled coke in my prison glove from Vegas to SF. Had 3 choices, Recovery for 6 months, prison or die.
I chose New Method Wellness: a dual diagnosis program in San Juan Capistrano. The owners, Susie, Ed, Deanna & Bing along with my therapists esp Linda Snell SAVED MY LIFE!  Everyone at NMW, the entire STAFF cares deeply about the clients & their recovery. This place IS a family. <Date>1544498351700< /Date>< review>
My son has been in and out of rehabs for the past 10 years. I never felt that he received the care and treatment he needed. As with any addiction not treated correctly, it only gets worse with time. His health began to be effected, so much so, that he began to have seizures. He was in ICU twice within a matter of 4 months. I have never felt so hopeless in my life.
I had heard of New Method Wellness. I had read about their facilities and staff, and felt that there approach might actually work for him.  Once my son made the decision to seek treatment he reached out to Brook at New Method while still in the hospital. From the moment he spoke to Brook, he was in constant contact with son. Offering him the encouragement and support he needed to make the decision to leave everything behind and travel almost 2000 miles to make a change in his life. Three days after the first phone call to New Method, my son was on a plane.

The staff at New Method have been amazing. Each and everyone one of them have played a part in his recovery. His individual therapy I think helped greatly. This is not a cookie cutter addition. There are different things going on with each individual and I think NMW understands that, and treats it accordingly.

As you and tell, I can not say enough good things about this place. I truly believe it not only changed my sons life but it changed mine as well, and I will be forever grateful.<//review>

<GmapID>0x80dcf1e4978705e7:0xc70a2a7c8d59840a< /GmapID>< Text>
A little over a year ago, I sat outside my house in Seattle in the dark and alone. I was high, for what I prayed would be my last time. I was lost, broken, and desperate. I sat on the side of my yard, against my house where no one could see me and just cried. I begged someone to help me. Anyone. I couldn't live that life anymore. My sister was in the house with my children. I knew they were safe but I also knew I wasn't. I sat there until my ride came. I kissed my precious babies goodbye and I left. I don't remember anything after that point. It would be 3 days before I have my first memory of California. By the grace of God I somehow navigated getting on the right plane, to the right person at the Orange County airport, and into the doors of New Method Wellness. It would be the beginning of my new life. In that moment, everything I had known had changed. New Method Wellness saved my life. The staff, the groups, the counseling, and other clients, all made for such a healing experience. I learned who I really was, obtained the tools on how to live a sober life, and made lifelong friends along the way. Today, a year later, I have my own apartment, a supportive family, my children, and a support network in sobriety that is solid. Thank you so much New Method Wellness for helping me get a new life and for teaching me a new and better way to live.<//Text>

<user_name>Shawn B< /user_name><Date>1558645386141< /Date><rating>1< /rating>< text>
My girlfriend had an amazing and eye opening experience during her 45 days here. However they had her on 4 different prescription medications, including Seroquel (quetiapine) which is well documented in peer reviewed scientific articles to cause false positive drug test results for methadone. Of course she kept getting multiple positive drug tests for methadone but when she tried to show them the scientific articles they got mad and asked why she wasn't just admitting she relapsed.

You would think with the salaries these people make that they would take 5 seconds out of their lives to look this up themselves (or even glance at the article given to them), but instead they kicked her out. I'm so proud of the progress my girlfriend made here and so disappointed at the lack of compassion and knowledge from the staff at this center.< /text>

< Review>
We are forever indebted to the incredible interventions by the staff at New Method Wellness when our adult son was in severe crisis with depression and alcoholism. We spoke on the phone with many different treatment centers, but the ONLY intake counselor who ever asked us if our son was present and asked to speak directly with him was Brook with NMW. After that 45 minute phone call, our son was relieved and said NMW was the place for him. A few days later, he was checked in and accepting the help he needed to save his own life. It has been a transformational experience for him to be treated and mentored by people who have walked this walk before him. This does not mean it has been an easy path--recovery is challenging and difficult and an individual's commitment to getting well is is most important factor, but the clinical staff at NMW has been amazing, and in hindsight, it was of vital importance that they be able to relate to the same struggles as our son and serve as examples of finding lifelong success in recovery--the messenger is just as important as the message, and all down the line, everyone at NMW can speak with honest empathy about their own path to recovery. Equally important, the strong focus at NMW on healing as a family has restored a lot of trust and provided a solid foundation for moving forward. For the first time in years, our son can imagine a good future for himself and knows he was worth saving, and we are equally hopeful. We cannot thank NMW enough. They have been so kind and stabilizing toward us during the frightening time of the crisis, and a lifesaver to our son who feels well and is proudly, fiercely sober.<//Review>

< review>
I have been an alcoholic since I was 14.  I kept trying to tell myself that it was just a stage that I was going through, but nothing would get better, except for the hiding of my alcoholism. At least in thought I was pretty good at it.
I‚Äôve gone through so much trauma, confusion and loss in my life that I assumed that one time when the incident would slowly pass I instantly would become a ‚Äúnormal‚Äù drinker again. We all fool ourselves into that lie over and over again. Then another crisis would happen and I was right back into the mess that I had made of my life and and all of those who‚Äôs lives that were unfortunate enough to have been touched by me.
When I was 48 years old I saw an ad on Facebook for a place called New Method Wellness so just out of curiosity I called them and spoke to Brook. Maybe the reason why I called them directly was because I thought that there was no possibile way that I would get such a wonderful opportunity.  Well I was completely wrong, I was on an airplane at 2:45 that morning and I was there by 10 o‚Äôclock that morning. I walked through the doors and instantly thought to myself this was not going to be for me. I am a country girl,  I don‚Äôt go to centers that look like this or deal with people that treat me as good as these people did. I walked through the building and everybody knew my name and  introduced themselves to me. I met people from all walks and areas of life. Some, t assumed I would have lots in common with, and some I had nothing in common with, either. After going through the program i realized that we all were there for so many similarities that I have so much in common with all of them and I built such close ties with all most of them. I even talk to my counselor as much as possible. New method saved my life I can honestly say that. I don‚Äôt think I could‚Äôve ever gone anywhere else that would‚Äôve understood me and treated me with compassion and love and had so many different areas to work with on me. I learned about trauma and what that has to do with what I suffer from and why I‚Äôve held onto it for so long. I learned about relationships and which ones are good to keep and which ones that you just need to let go of. I love and care for everybody that I met there.   These people truly cared about me and truly cared about my sobriety.  From my treatment to where I lived to the relationships I made and the extracurricular activities, meetings, volunteering, all had to do with my sobriety.  I have gone to four other treatment centers and I cannot even compare them to the experience I had there. You can be who you are you can love who you want you can have the people that you will be very close with forever and the people that will have made an impact on your life forever.  Again, they saved my life and I will always be so grateful to them so will all my children my family and my husband and friends. I find myself missing being there and I can‚Äôt wait to go there again just to visit them on my anniversary of November  30th 2018. No matter how much hype or how comfortable you are with your surroundings,  it is and was the best  thing I could‚Äôve done for myself.  I love you all and I will thank you all for the rest of my life. I can‚Äôt wait to see everyone again and to those who think that this is just not for them, do what I did just call.</review>

< review>
It has taken a few months to digest the aftermath of this particular treatment center as it's related to our 26 year old Son who was admitted back in Aug. of 2016 through Nov. 2016 and although we commend New Method and their Counselor, for his detox and also keeping him from prescription drugs, we still find ourselves somewhat dissapointed in the facility, as he did not have the adequate diagnoses or treatment for his underlining emotional conditions. <username>Nikolai Rivas< /username>< pics>
None<//pics>
< time>
1614716243903< /time>
< text>
Without question, the BEST experience I have ever had when visiting a dentist. From scheduling my first appointment to the actual cleaning, the staff at Melissa S. Chun's office went above and beyond my expectations.

Halley (sp?) was the first point of contact. She works at the front desk and was the one to schedule my appointment. It was her friendliness and honesty that made me feel comfortable enough to give Melissa S. Chun's office a chance.

When I arrived for my appointment, I was greeted at the door by Amber, who ended up being my hygienist. Amber took me through a brief tour of the office before setting me up to fill out my paperwork. Once that was out of the way, she explained how my visit would proceed, and was more than willing to answer any questions I had. She took my x-rays (which are digital, aka SAFER) and cleaned my teeth, all the while maintaining an infectious positive attitude. It was like visiting a friend who just happened to be cleaning my teeth as opposed to a random stranger digging around in my mouth.

I was told prior to arriving that the dentist, Dr. Chun, may not be able to make it due to jury duty. However, she arrived halfway through my cleaning and introduced herself. I've never had jury duty, and I could imagine how draining it might be, but Dr. Chun was fantastic nonetheless. Her professionalism was second only to her friendliness. She walked me through my x-ray photos and examined my teeth before handing things back to the hygienist, Amber.

Overall, I am thoroughly pleased with my visit. In the past, I have often been hesitant to schedule a follow-up with a dentist, since the experience is usually quite lackluster. However,  after such exceptional treatment, I've already scheduled my follow-up and am planning to continue using Melissa S. Chun's dental practice for any issues that may arise in the future.</text>

<rating>2<//rating>< text>
Service: 2 stars
Sat in the bar area around 5 pm on a saturday. Majority of the place was empty but the table was filthy. The waitress took about 15 minutes to acknowledge me but did eventually wiped down the table. In the 2 hours i was there i probably saw her 3 times which was fone since she didn't exactly light up the room with a cheery disposition (none of them did, in fact). Had to ask passing servers multiple times to check on where my orders were as well as if i could get silverware.

Food: 2 stars
I ordered a medium sized boneless wing. They typically come with about 15 wings but tonight they came with about 10-11, which were cold and partially "unsauced" by the time they hit the table. When all was said and done i spent about 40 dollars for a medium wing and 2 blue moons.
I doubt I'll be back any time soon.<//text>
